<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<t24help>
<header>
<product>FD</product>
<table>FD.ACTIVITY</table>
</header>
<overview>
<ovdesc>

            <b>Description</b>
            <p>This application descriptions for activity codes automatically generated by the system to be defined. </p>
        </ovdesc>
<ovimage></ovimage>
</overview>
<menu>
<t>
<field>MANUAL.REQUEST</field>
<desc>
            <p>Defines whether an advice for the activity can be manually requested. For future use. </p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p>
                <p value="1">Y or NO. (Optional field)</p>
            </p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>RESERVED1</field>
<desc>
            <p>This field is reserved for future expansion. </p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p>This is a NOINPUT field.</p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>HANDOFF.ROUTINE</field>
<desc>
            <p>Any specific information required for a particular country or site that is non standard, should coded in this routine name. </p>
            <p>If a routine is required for local changes in the default handoff produced by the application, the details should be coded in a routine, the name of which is defined here. If such a routine is attached, the handoff will be modified based on the changes incorporated in this routine. The handed off to delivery will be passed as the seventh record. </p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p>
                <p value="1">1 to 25-character program name (Optional input)</p>
                <p value="2">Must exist on the PGM.FILE as a type "S" routine.</p>
            </p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>RESERVED2</field>
<desc>
            <p>This field is reserved for future expansion. </p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p>This is a NOINPUT field.</p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>ACTIVITY.CODE</field>
<desc>
            <p>Description</p>
            <p>The activity code generated by the system automatically. </p>
            <p>Valid activity codes are as follows: </p>
            <p>           101  Confirmation of a New Contract            102  Contract Initiation            </p>
            <p>103  Contract Financial Change            </p>
            <p>104  Contract Amendment            </p>
            <p>105  Interest Payment            </p>
            <p>106  Contract Maturity            </p>
            <p>107  Contract Reversal            </p>
            <p>108  Rate Change Advice            </p>
            <p>109  Commission and Charges            </p>
            <p>110  New Fiduciary Order (Renewals)            </p>
            <p>111  Amendment to Fiduciary Order            </p>
            <p>202  Payment to Fiduciary Bank            </p>
            <p>210  Advice to Receive </p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p>
                <p value="1">3 numeric characters (Mandatory input)</p>
            </p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>DAYS.PRIOR.EVENT</field>
<desc>
            <p>Description</p>
            <p>The number of days prior to the event that the advice should be generated. For future use. </p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p>
                <p value="1">1 to 2 number of days. (Optional input)</p>
            </p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>DESCRIPTION</field>
<desc>
            <p>Description</p>
            <p>The description of the activity code. </p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p>
                <p value="1">3-35 alphanumeric characters.  </p>
                <p value="2">Multi language field. </p>
                <p value="3">Mandatory input</p>
            </p>
        </desc>
</t>
<t>
<field>HANDOFF.ROUTINE.</field>
<desc>
            <p>Standard T24 numeric field. </p>
            <p>
                <p>Validation Rules:</p>
            </p>
            <p>
                <p value="1">A maximum of 25 characters may be entered.</p>
                <p value="2">Must be the key to a valid entry on the PGM.FILE file.</p>
            </p>
        </desc>
</t>
</menu>
</t24help>

